                <p>As the final project of my Bachelor in Communication & Multimedia Design I created a fluid typography design tool in the browser.</p>
                <p>Static design tools don’t offer what HTML & CSS can offer - it’s actually not even close. It always made more sense to me to sketch a design out on paper and then jumping straight into CSS. One problem: we can’t expect designers to learn how to write code, or developers to suddenly be good at design. That’s where my idea grew to create a way to design fluid typography using clamp(), without having to know anything about code.</p>         
