            <h2 class="text-step-3">Process</h2>
            <p>I started off this project by reading lots of articles, i.e. <a href="https://alistapart.com/article/dao/" target="_blank">A Dao of Web Design</a> and <a href="https://alistapart.com/article/responsive-web-design/" target="_blank">Responsive Web Design</a>. These manifesto-like documents inspired me to take a more idealistic approach.</p>
            <p>After analysing different articles and websites, conducting some interviews & expert interviews, benchmarking and doing target audience research, I created a requirement list:</p>
            <ul class="stack-s list">
                <li class="product">The product needs a standard text layout that the user can customize.</li>
                <li class="product">The product must offer options for different fonts for body text and headlines.</li>
                <li class="product">The product must offer Google Font options for choosing different fonts.</li>
                <li class="product">The product must include a control panel that allows the user to adjust type scale, line height, font size, and content width.</li>
                <li class="product">The product must make interactive elements such as buttons and links customizable, including focus, active, and hover states.</li>
                <li class="user">As a user, I want to be able to play with responsiveness without having to code.</li>
                <li class="user">As a user, I want to be able to play with typographic values and see a live preview when I change something.</li>
                <li class="user">As a user, I want to be able to test the typography on my phone and other devices.</li>
                <li class="user">As a user, I want to be able to export my entered values.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>With these requirements in mind, I started thinking up some concepts.</p>
